// Accept fixture: a local type declaration shadows an import alias of the same
// bare name (local-shadows-imported rule).
//
// `hew::aliassrc` exports `Payload` (field: `code: i64`).  The importer opts
// it in under the alias `U` (`import hew::aliassrc::{ Payload as U }`).
// Simultaneously, the importer declares its own `type U { local: i64 }`.
//
// The type checker resolves bare `U` to the LOCAL declaration first
// (local_type_defs wins over published_bare).  HIR `resolve_named_type_ref`
// must apply the alias ONLY as a fallback — after the `record_registry` check
// declines the name — so the local `type U` takes precedence.
//
// If the alias is applied FIRST (the pre-fix bug), `U` would be rewritten to
// `aliassrc.Payload`, which has no `local` field, and the field read would
// fail with a type error or at runtime.
//
// Proof: construct `U { local: 7 }` and print `local`.  Output "7" proves
// the local type was used, not the aliassrc.Payload.
import hew::aliassrc::{ Payload as U };

type U {
    local: i64;
}

fn get_local(x: U) -> i64 {
    x.local
}

fn main() {
    let v = U { local: 7 };
    println(get_local(v));
}
